  "text": "Chinese Medicine *Correspondence: tjaya_2002@yahoo.co.in; sheujr@tmu.edu.tw † Ling-Wei Hsu and Wei-Cheng Shiao contributed equally to this work [CITATION_1] Graduate Institute of Medical Sciences, College of Medicine, Taipei Medical University, Taipei, Taiwan Full list of author information is available at the end of the article is higher in China than it is in people from other highincome countries [CITATION_2] . Ischemic brain tissue can be partially prevented from sprouting into infarction by several neuroprotective drugs [CITATION_3] . It is noteworthy however, that numerous experimentally effective neuroprotective drugs have failed in clinical trials in human because of serious side effects [CITATION_4] .",
